Best in show: behind the scenes at the 2017 Westminster dog show – in pictures Share on Facebook Share on Twitter Share via Email View more sharing options Share on LinkedIn Share on Pinterest Share on Google+ Share on WhatsApp Share on Messenger Close
The Westminster dog show is America’s oldest continuously held sporting event after the Kentucky Derby. Now in its 141st year, this year’s competition will see 2908 dogs from 200 different breeds or varieties compete over two days for the coveted best in show title as well as various best in breed prizes.
Tuesday 14 February 2017 04.10 GMT
Dogs are separated into seven categories: hound, toy, non-sporting, sporting, herding, working and terrier. Here, Basenjis, part of the hound group, line up with their handlers for judging. Photograph: Justin Lane/EPA
